GitHub Push Workflow for Terraform Projects Using VS Code

This is a practical step-by-step notes document for pushing Terraform code to GitHub using Visual Studio Code and PowerShell terminal.

1. Basic Understanding
Tool	Purpose
VS Code	Write and edit code
PowerShell Terminal	Run Git and Terraform commands
Git	Version control
GitHub	Remote code repository
2. Open Project in VS Code

Open project folder:

terraform-aws-vpc-project
3. Open Terminal in VS Code

In VS Code:

Terminal → New Terminal

You will see PowerShell terminal at the bottom.

Example:

PS D:\Devops_Tutorial\Terraform\terraform-aws-vpc-project>
4. Create .gitignore

Create a file named:

.gitignore

Add:

# Terraform
.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
crash.log

# Variable files
terraform.tfvars
*.tfvars

# Sensitive files
*.pem
*.key

# Terraform lock file
.terraform.lock.hcl

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
5. Why .gitignore Is Important

Never upload:

File/Folder	Reason
.terraform/	Large provider binaries
.tfstate	Infrastructure state data
.pem	Private SSH keys
terraform.tfvars	Sensitive values
6. Initialize Git Repository

Run:

git init
7. Add Files to Git

Run:

git add .
8. Verify Files Before Commit

Run:

git status

Verify:

.terraform/ should NOT appear
.tfstate should NOT appear
9. Commit Files

Run:

git commit -m "Initial Terraform VPC project"
10. Create Repository in GitHub

Go to:

GitHub New Repository Page

Repository name example:

terraform-aws-vpc-project
11. Rename Branch to Main

Run:

git branch -M main
12. Connect Local Repository to GitHub

Run:

git remote add origin https://github.com/ShrutiCoder/terraform-aws-vpc-project.git
13. Push Code to GitHub

Run:

git push -u origin main
14. GitHub Authentication

GitHub no longer supports password authentication.

Use:

Personal Access Token (PAT)

instead of GitHub password.

15. Create GitHub Personal Access Token

Go to:

GitHub Personal Access Tokens

Steps:

Generate new token (classic)

Enable:

repo
Generate token
Copy token immediately
16. During Git Push

When prompted:

Username
ShrutiCoder
Password

Paste:

Personal Access Token
NOT GitHub password
17. Common Errors and Fixes
Error: Password authentication is not supported
Solution

Use Personal Access Token instead of GitHub password.

Error: Permission denied (403)
Solution
Enable repo permission in token
Clear old credentials from Windows Credential Manager
Error: Large files detected
Cause

.terraform/ folder uploaded.

Solution

Add .terraform/ to .gitignore.

Error: BucketAlreadyExists
Cause

S3 bucket names are globally unique.

Solution

Use unique bucket name.

18. Useful Git Commands
Command	Purpose
git init	Initialize repository
git add .	Add files
git status	Check changes
git commit -m "msg"	Commit changes
git push	Upload code
git pull	Download latest code
git remote -v	Check remote URL
